						<div class="postbody">Interesting logic.  Not a bad port either.
<br />
<br />I don't know how Nintendo did it (randomness) back in the day, but I've played the NWC1990 cart a few times and if you score a certain a amount in SMB1, you always seem to get a certain sequence of pieces in Tetris.  It seems to me they had something like arrays defined with pre-determined patterns of pieces and probably had it periodically pick one of those out.  I don't know how many arrays they would have had, but probably a lot to make it really feign randomness.</div>

